=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Well, there you have it=E2=80=A6 <br/><br/>It was alrea=
dy a couple of hours into the fair, so I asked how sales were going for him=
=2E The dealer hiked a thumb over hi=
s shoulder and said that he =E2=80=9Csold=
 two works already.=E2=80=9D He was pointing toward a large gold painting a=
t the center of his booth, which he said had sold for nearly a quarter-mill=
ion dollars. =E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=99s pretty much the top
end of what you expect to sell at this fair.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>The dealer w=
as happy, and his complacency seemed to reflect the overall mood of the art=
 market. I have more sales to report below, and a look at what=E2=80=99s go=
ing on behind all of the cautiously optimistic quotes you=E2=80=99ve been r=
eading in the art press.<br/><br/>=F0=9F=93=B1<i>Is there something you hav=
e to say?</i>: If you want to share an idea, tell me I=E2=80=99m wrong, or =
