          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">I=E2=80=99ll stop t=
here. You get the point. Collectors are buying art. Dealers are selling art=
=2E It=E2=80=99s really not so bad out the=
re.<br/><br/>I closed out my two-da=
y sprint through the art market at dealer <b>Andrew Schoelkopf</b>=E2=80=99=
s dinner at Zou Zou in Brookfield=E2=80=99s Manhattan West development, not=
 far from the Javits. Schoelkopf was celebrating a successful fair where he=
 debuted his representation of the estate of first-generation Abstract Expr=
essionist <b>Mary Abbott</b>.<br/><br/>One of the most interesting things S=
choelkopf had to say was that Dallas has become one of the most active art-=
buying cities in America, at least for him. That=E2=80=99s a subject for an=
other time. But any Dallas folks who want to chime in, feel free to reply t=
o this email and let me know your thoughts. <br/><br/>Let=E2=80=99s talk ag=
ain on Tuesday,<br/>Marion<br/></td>
